glosses: to fall, drop, go down, decrease
to be miscarried; to be aborted
to fall into, be overcome by (doubts, worry, trouble), to wind up in, end up in
to get tired and weak, fall from power
to receive, get as one's share
to live in sexual intimacy with, sleep around with

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish دوشمك (düşmek, “to fall, go down, decline, to fall or pass into a condition”), from Proto-Turkic *tüĺ- (“to fall, move down”).
